## Prerequisites
Make sure you have the `gcloud` CLI and `kubectl` installed and configured with access to your Google Cloud project.

---

## Step 1: Check Current Version

To see a quick overview of your cluster or local context version, run:

```bash
gcloud container clusters list
```

```bash
kubectl version --short

```bash
gcloud container clusters describe lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a \
    --format="value(currentMasterVersion,currentNodeVersion)"

## Step 2: Check Available Upgrade Versions
Before upgrading, check which versions are currently supported and available in your zone:

```bash
gcloud container get-server-config \
    --zone us-central1-a

```bash
Valid master versions:
1.34.2-gke.100
1.34.1-gke.200
1.33.5-gke.150

## Step 3: Upgrade the Control Plane
Choose one of the available versions from the previous step to upgrade your cluster's master components.

```bash
gcloud container clusters upgrade lottery-cluster \
    --master \
    --cluster-version=1.34.2-gke.100 \
    --zone us-central1-a

##  Step 4: Upgrade the Node Pool
First, list your available node pools to find the exact name:

```bash
gcloud container node-pools list \
    --cluster lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a

```bash
NAME          MACHINE_TYPE
default-pool  e2-small

Next, upgrade the specific node pool to match your control plane version:

```bash
gcloud container node-pools upgrade default-pool \
    --cluster lottery-cluster \
    --cluster-version=1.34.2-gke.100 \
    --zone us-central1-a

ℹ️ How it works: GKE performs a rolling upgrade. It safely creates new nodes, drains workloads from old nodes to migrate them to the new ones, and removes the old nodes once the transition is complete.


##  Step 5: Verify the Upgrade
Confirm that your nodes have updated and reached a Ready status:

```bash
kubectl get nodes

```bash
NAME                                    STATUS   VERSION
gke-lottery-cluster-default-pool-xxxx   Ready    v1.34.2-gke.100

Alternatively, you can verify via gcloud:

```bash
gcloud container clusters describe lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a \
    --format="value(currentMasterVersion,currentNodeVersion)"


Automation & Shortcuts
Upgrade to the Latest Available Version
Instead of specifying a specific version string, you can let GKE automatically pick the latest supported version for your release channel:

```bash
gcloud container clusters upgrade lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a

Enable Automatic Upgrades
To hand off version management completely to Google Cloud, enable auto-upgrading on the cluster:

```bash
gcloud container clusters update lottery-cluster \
    --enable-autoupgrade \
    --zone us-central1-a
Or enable it specifically for an individual node pool:

```bash
gcloud container node-pools update default-pool \
    --enable-autoupgrade \
    --cluster lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a
